---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout
  title="Abhishekh Ojha | Full Stack Developer"
  description="Learn more about Abhishekh Ojha (also known as Abhishek Ojha), a Full Stack Developer and AI Engineer building scalable web applications."
  url="https://www.abhishekhojha.com/abhishekh-ojha"
>
  <main
    class="container mx-auto px-4 pt-24 sm:pt-28 md:pt-36 py-24 min-h-screen text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200"
  >
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6">
      <h1
        class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 tracking-tight"
      >
        Abhishekh Ojha
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Hello! I am <strong>Abhishekh Ojha</strong> (often spelled as <strong
          >Abhishek Ojha</strong
        >), a passionate Full Stack Developer and AI Automation Expert based in
        India. I specialize in building highly scalable, responsive web
        applications and integrating advanced AI capabilities into modern
        digital solutions.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
        With extensive experience in the MERN stack and Next.js ecosystem, I
        focus on delivering seamless user experiences and robust backend
        architectures. My journey in software engineering has allowed me to work
        on diverse projects, from high-performance e-commerce platforms to
        sophisticated AI-driven tools that streamline business operations.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">
        My Expertise
      </h2>
      <ul
        class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
      >
        <li>
          <strong>Frontend Development:</strong> HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, React.js,
          Next.js
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Backend Development:</strong> Node.js, Express.js, PHP, Laravel,
          Python
        </li>
        <li><strong>Databases:</strong> MongoDB, MySQL</li>
        <li><strong>CMS & E-commerce:</strong> WordPress, Shopify</li>
        <li><strong>Version Control & Deployment:</strong> Git, Vercel</li>
      </ul>

      <h2
        class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"
      >
        Technologies I Use
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-5 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        A versatile toolkit spanning front-end, back-end, databases, and
        deployment — chosen for real-world reliability.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2.5 mb-8">
        {
          [
            "HTML5",
            "CSS3",
            "JavaScript",
            "React.js",
            "Next.js",
            "Node.js",
            "Express.js",
            "PHP",
            "Laravel",
            "Python",
            "MongoDB",
            "MySQL",
            "WordPress",
            "Shopify",
            "Git",
            "Vercel",
          ].map((tech) => (
            <span class="px-3.5 py-1.5 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/80 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 text-sm font-medium rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700/80 shadow-sm hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-transform duration-200">
              {tech}
            </span>
          ))
        }
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mt-6">
        As <strong>Abhishek Ojha</strong>, I constantly strive to stay at the
        forefront of technology, embracing new frameworks and methodologies to
        solve complex problems efficiently. Whether it's architecting a new
        application from scratch or optimizing an existing system for better
        performance and SEO, I bring dedication and a detail-oriented approach
        to every project.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
        <a
          href="/"
          class="text-[var(--brand-dark)] dark:text-[var(--brand-light)] font-semibold hover:underline"
        >
          &larr; Back to Homepage
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
